                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/154a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-22T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 22, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>345. Your 500, May 21, 7 p.m. Department approves your action in postponing
                    presentation of question to Soviet Government in view of British Ambassador’s
                    statements, and will consult British Government again and send you new
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
